STRUCTURE. Body shape and vestiture as in generic description. Head (
Figs 5–8
) 2.2 times as long as pronotum, 2.35 times as long as its maximum width; anteocular part 1.3 times as long as postocular part; antennal scape 0.9 times as long as anteocular part; labial segment II 1.9 times as long as segment III, distinctly surpassing posterior margin of eye, with apical ¾ strongly curved dorsally, approaching ventral surface of head (
Fig. 6
); labial segment III strongly inflated (
Figs 6–7
). Pronotum (
Figs 5–6
) 1.1 times as broad across humeral angles as its length; anterior lobe two times as long as posterior lobe, moderately swollen dorsally; posterior lobe 1.1 times as broad as width of anterior lobe; prosternum (
Fig. 7
) almost reaching posterior margins of mid coxal cavities; scutellum (
Fig. 9
) broad, suberect, with apical prongs short. Fore wing (
Fig. 9
) scale-like, reaching apical ⅔ of scutellum. Abdomen ovoid, 1.4 times as long as its maximum width.

FEMALE GENITALIA (
Figs 10–11
). As in generic description.
